                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                            <p>Seven fragments recomposed as three adjoining <material>limestone</material> <objectType>panel</objectType>s carrying a copy of the decree of 
                                Anastasius, 
                                de rebus Libyae Pentapolis denuo constituendis:  a 
                               <dimensions>
                                  <width>1.56</width>
                                  <height>1.21</height>
                                  <depth>0.11</depth>
                               </dimensions>; 
                              b, recomposed from 7 fragments,  
                              <dimensions>
                                 <width>1.57</width>
                                 <height>1.21</height>
                                 <depth>0.11</depth>
                              </dimensions>; 
                              c: 
                              <dimensions>
                                 <width>0.75</width>
                                 <height>0.96</height>
                                 <depth>0.11</depth>
                              </dimensions>. For another, fragmentary, copy at Apollonia, 
                                see <ref type="inscription">A04600</ref>, and, for a single block, at Teucheira, <ref type="inscription">T02200</ref>. The surface is weathered with some substantial holes.
                              </p>
                        </support>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                         <layout>The text is laid out in columns on each block; lines are regular and straight. In contrast to the version at Apollonia,  
                             but similarly to the version at Teucheira, there are no line breaks for paragraphs.</layout>
